==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Congee
<hw>Con*gee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[Tamil
<ets>ka⟦ncir⟧shi</ets> boilings.]</ety> <def>Boiled rice; rice
gruel.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A jail; a lockup.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Congee discharges</b></col>, <cd>rice water
discharges.</cd> <au>Dunglison.</au> -- <col><b>Congee water</b></col>,
<cd>water in which rice has been boiled.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Congelation</ent>⟦br⟧
